definitions.definition: Any of certain plants in the mint family, many used as ornamentals for their colorful, variegated leaves, sometime included in genus Plectranthus ( spurflowers ), sometimes in  their own genus Coleus ,

subdefinitions.definition: especially, Plectranthus scutellarioides , also known as Coleus scutellarioides and Coleus blumei .
